AUSTRALIA
WHERE THE TROPICS MEET THE SNOW

AUSTRALIA
Ocean and air liners travelling to Australia are packed by travellers on
business or on pleasure, and those who will make their homes there.
Plan well ahead for transport and accommodation, preferably
through a dependable agent who will safeguard your comfort and
convenience.
Ask about Australia at Australian offices in London,
New
York, San Francisco, Washington, Ottawa,
Vancouver.
Dublin,
Paris,
Capetown,
Johannesburg,
Pretoria, The Hague,
Colombo,
Cairo,
Nanking,
Batavia,
Singapore,
Tokyo, Noumea,
Wellington,
Manila, Dili, Bangkok, Moscow, Karachi, Bombay, Calcutta, New Delhi,
Shanghai, Hong Kong, Rio de Janeiro, Berlin, Rome.
There is no other country just like Australia, in its people, its way of
life, its spaciousness, and the strange flora and fauna it has inherited
from before the dawn of history.
This age-old land of the Southern Cross, home of one of the world's
youngest nations, provides a fascinating field of travel off the conven-
tional tourist routes, but readily accessible at a world junction of air
and ocean travel.
